        "## Step 5: Executive-ready visualization\n",
        "\n",
        "Now the part stakeholders actually see. A chart is exec ready when the title states the\n",
        "finding, the labels sit on the data instead of in a legend box, and each chart makes\n",
        "exactly one point. Everything below follows those three rules."
      ],
      "id": "69ed3c17"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: chart-style\n",
        "#| code-summary: Shared chart style and helpers\n",
        "\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import matplotlib.ticker as mtick\n",
        "\n",
        "## one palette for the whole piece. navy carries TV, blue is digital,\n",
        "## slate fades mail into the background. red is reserved for election day\n",
        "## so it always means the same thing\n",
        "NAVY, BLUE, SLATE, RED, GRAY = '#0f172a', '#2563eb', '#94a3b8', '#dc2626', '#64748b'\n",
        "colors = {'TV/Broadcast': NAVY, 'Digital': BLUE, 'Direct Mail': SLATE}\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.rcParams.update({\n",
        "    'axes.spines.top': False,\n",
        "    'axes.spines.right': False,\n",
        "    'figure.facecolor': 'white',\n",
        "    'font.size': 10,\n",
        "})\n",
        "\n",
        "def fmt_dollars(v):\n",
        "    ### $1.2B above a billion, $850M below\n",
        "    return f'${v/1e9:.1f}B' if v >= 1e9 else f'${v/1e6:.0f}M'\n",
        "\n",
        "def headline(ax, title, sub):\n",
        "    ### takeaway goes big and bold, the literal description goes small and gray\n",
        "    ax.set_title(title, fontsize=14, fontweight='bold', loc='left', pad=30, color=NAVY)\n",
        "    ax.text(0, 1.06, sub, transform=ax.transAxes, fontsize=9.5, color=GRAY)"
      ],
      "id": "chart-style",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "First view: the size of the pie. Every bar gets a dollar label so the y axis can go away\n",
